                        <bindingDesc>
                            <binding contemporary="true" notBefore="1800" notAfter="1850">
                                <p>Half-binding from the 19th cent. Boards covered with marbled
                                    paper (brown, gray, and blue); leather spine and corners. Blue
                                    paper used for pastedown and flyleaves.</p>
                                <p>Fore-edges of the book block are painted blue. </p>
                                <p>Gilt, floral patterns embossed at head and foot of spine and gilt
                                    tooled image of an urn in the middle. </p>
                                <p>Gilt title embossed into the spine: <q>SOGUBOK ALFE 3 HROLFE 3
                                        &amp;c</q>.</p>
                                <p> A partially damaged provenance sticker, affixed to the foot of
                                    spine, reads: <q>Nykjöbi[ng] Cath-Sko[le] Bibliothek</q>. </p>
                            </binding>
                        </bindingDesc>
